In Zimbabwe, Asians and Arab speaking nationals have always shunned politics, citing marginalisation and segregation despite most of them being very successful entrepreneurs. 

The majority of these nationals are Muslims whose religion is treated with suspicion due to extremism leading to acts of terror, in some parts of the world. However, for the first time in Zimbabwe, over the weekend, Muslims came out of their shells of fear and demanded respect of their rights. 

Simon Muchemwa reports from Harare.... --ChannelAfrica--